## Active Uncertainty
<!-- Problems the hermit knows about but hasn't resolved yet -->
```dataview
TABLE title, category, accepted_date
FROM ".claude-code-hermit/proposals"
WHERE id AND status = "accepted"
SORT accepted_date ASC
```

## Fragile Zones (All Time)
<!-- Cumulative weak domains — where sessions have historically ended incomplete -->
```dataview
TABLE length(rows) AS "Incomplete Sessions"
FROM ".claude-code-hermit/sessions"
WHERE id AND (status = "blocked" OR status = "partial")
FLATTEN tags AS tag
GROUP BY tag
SORT length(rows) DESC
LIMIT 5
```

## Recently Resolved
<!-- Proposals that were resolved — problems the hermit addressed -->
```dataview
TABLE title, resolved_date, category
FROM ".claude-code-hermit/proposals"
WHERE id AND status = "resolved"
SORT resolved_date DESC
LIMIT 10
```

## Regressions
<!-- Incomplete sessions in areas where a proposal was already resolved.
     v1: tag overlap is a proximity signal, not proof of regression. -->
```dataviewjs
const proposals = dv.pages('".claude-code-hermit/proposals"')
  .where(p => p.status === "resolved" && p.tags);
const resolved_tags = new Set(proposals.flatMap(p => p.tags || []));
const incomplete = dv.pages('".claude-code-hermit/sessions"')
  .where(s => (s.status === "blocked" || s.status === "partial") && s.tags)
  .sort(s => s.date, 'desc')
  .limit(20);
const hits = incomplete.filter(s =>
  (s.tags || []).some(t => resolved_tags.has(t)));
dv.table(["Date", "Task", "Suspect Tags"],
  hits.map(s => [s.date, s.task,
    (s.tags || []).filter(t => resolved_tags.has(t)).join(", ")]));
```

## Operator Dependence
<!-- operator_turns = 0 means the hermit completed the session without a single redirect -->
```dataview
TABLE
  length(filter(rows, (r) => r.operator_turns = 0)) + " / " +
  length(rows) AS "Self-directed / Total",
  round(length(filter(rows, (r) => r.operator_turns = 0)) /
    length(rows) * 100) + "%" AS "Self-directed rate"
FROM ".claude-code-hermit/sessions"
WHERE id
GROUP BY dateformat(date, "yyyy-'W'WW") AS "Week"
SORT Week DESC
LIMIT 8
```

## Escalation Profile
<!-- Configured trust level — did the operator set the hermit loose or keep it on a leash? -->
```dataview
TABLE
  length(filter(rows, (r) => r.escalation = "autonomous")) AS "Autonomous",
  length(filter(rows, (r) => r.escalation = "balanced")) AS "Balanced",
  length(filter(rows, (r) => r.escalation = "conservative")) AS "Conservative"
FROM ".claude-code-hermit/sessions"
WHERE id
GROUP BY dateformat(date, "yyyy-'W'WW") AS "Week"
SORT Week DESC
LIMIT 8
```

